title: Grateful Dead Live at Bakersfield Memorial Auditorium on 1978-01-14
lineage: MAC>> Nakamichi CR7a => Korg MR-1000 >> DSF [1-bit 5.6448 MHz Stereo] >> Korg MR-1000 => Korg AudioGate >> WAV [24/96]
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Dire Wolf, Cassidy, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Me & My Uncle, Loser, Looks Like Rain, Deal, Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Candyman, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Not Fade Away-> One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: gotta love 1/78! wow, I'm so glad this tape has circulated!  January of 1978 is a very interesting time for the band.  It just sounds so energized and raw.  This show is odd because a soundman gets busted by the Bakersfield police, which leads to a short show and an angry announcement by Phil.  the space before NFA is groovy as well.
Recording too fast! Sounds energized because the tape has been sped up.
No, it's not speeded up The tape was recorded and transferred at the proper speed
